HEADWORD: Fisherman
<hw>Fish"er*man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Fishermen</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One whose
occupation is to catch fish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A ship or vessel employed in the
business of taking fish, as in the cod fishery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fishery</ent>⟦br⟧
